HEADWORD: Mydatoxin
<hw>Myd`a*tox"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>myda^n</grk> to be clammy (from decay) + <ets>tox</ets>ic +
<ets>in</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A poisonous amido
acid, <chform>C6H13NO2</chform>, separated by Brieger from decaying
horseflesh. In physiological action, it is similar to curare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

